com.taplytics.sdk
Class Taplytics

java.lang.Object
  com.taplytics.sdk.Taplytics

public class Taplytics
extends java.lang.Object

Main class for using Taplytics

Call startTaplytics(Context, String) with the main application context and your Taplytics apiKey.

Once you have started Taplytics, you can run experiments using runCodeExperiment(String, TaplyticsCodeExperimentListener), and track goals using #goalAchieved(String, Object).

The Taplytics SDK will retrieve experiment configurations from our servers and send event and goal information back to our servers. Your application will require the android permission: android.permission.INTERNET.

Optionally Start Taplytics with your associated API Key and specific options. Call this method in when your Application is created.

Options include: - "liveUpdate" true or false. Taplytics will auto-detect an app store or development build, but to force production mode set to false, or true for development mode.

Parameters:
appContext - application context to track
apiKey - your Taplytics API Key
options - Map of Taplytics start options

runCodeExperiment

public static void runCodeExperiment(java.lang.String experimentName,
                                     Taplytics.TaplyticsCodeExperimentListener listener)
Run a Taplytics code experiment, defined by experimentName. Unless it is the first time the application has been launched the listener will run synchronously. If it is the first time the application has been launched on the device, the listener will not be called until the experiment configuration is loaded from Taplytics's servers. Unless run early in your application's lifecycle, this method should be used for the majority of experiments.

If you are running an experiment very early in your App's life-cycle you can use runCodeExperimentSync(String, TaplyticsCodeExperimentListener)

Parameters:
experimentName - experiment's unique name
listener - experiment variation listener

runCodeExperimentSync

public static void runCodeExperimentSync(java.lang.String experimentName,
                                         Taplytics.TaplyticsCodeExperimentListener listener)
Run a Taplytics code experiment, defined by experimentName. The listener will always be run synchronously, if the experiment configuration hasn't loaded from Taplytics's server yet the baseline configuration will be shown and baseline variables Map will be null.

Parameters:
experimentName - experiment's unique name
listener - experiment variation listener
